Tony Okafor, Awka A container has fallen down from an articulated vehicle on Monday in Onitsha, Anambra State. This came a few days after two tankers fell in the commercial city, leaving on their trails deaths and destruction of property. In the Monday incident, two persons were allegedly hit by the trailer’s container. The incident, it was gathered, happened on Owerri Road, Upper Iweka, Onitsha. The cause could not be ascertained as of the time of filing this report. The Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Haruna Mohammed, confirmed the incident. He said no fatality was recorded. Mohammed said a woman who was passing by sustained injury and was taken to the hospital He said said the victims were responding to treatment. He added, “Scene was cordoned off by Police patrol teams and efforts are ongoing to clear obstruction to enable free flow of traffic in the area.”